summary: I love movies (and other media) that was made years ago and are set in the ‘future’. It’s interesting. I just watched ‘The...
body:
I love movies (and other media) that was made years ago and are set in the ‘future’. It’s interesting. I just watched ‘The Island’ which was made in 2005 and it’s actually set in 2019 and it’s so crazy.

But Cyberpunk 2020 is obviously set in 2020. It’s just so strange for me that these ‘futuristic’ pieces of art are set in a future that we can directly compare to our own?

Does any of this make sense?

Someone talk to me about this!!!

summary: So like I really just want it to be March 28. I’m really hoping for more news on Cyberpunk 2077 at PAX, based on previous years...
body:
So like I really just want it to be March 28. I’m really hoping for more news on Cyberpunk 2077 at PAX, based on previous years with CD Projekt Red.

I genuinely think we’ll get either a release date at PAX or E3.

I’m kind of thinking a fall 2019 Release or a spring 2020 release based on them saying it’s going to be playable on Xbox One and PS4. Not to mention they’ve stated the game is playable start to finish. So I’m assuming it won’t be long before we see more.

The Witcher 3 was released in May if I remember correctly, so maybe we’ll see that again? However, I believe the odd timing of that release was purely because of delay.
